✨3 Hair Rules To Always Follow✨

❌✅ - when you're 🧖‍♀️🛁

While you can always bend the rules while styling your hair, there are a few cardinal ones you really shouldn’t be breaking - that is if you want your hair to be strong, healthy and lustrous. 💁🏽‍♀️

Rule #1 - Detangling 
❌ start from the top to bottom? 
✅ start from the bottom and detangle and then move to the top. This will help prevent breakage.

Rule #2: - Detangling using wide toothed comb 
❌ detangle your hair with your fingers? 
✅When detangling wet hair, it’s always better to use a wide tooth comb rather than your fingers, it not only detangles more efficiently but also ensures even distribution of conditioner all over 💫

Rule #3: - Towel drying 
❌ do you aggressive rub? 
✅ Pat it down instead.
it's always nicer pat it down as rubbing wet hair will damage your cuticles which will leave your hair feeling frizzy 
.
.
.
Tell me (honestly) how many of these have you broken? 😬

Considering cysteine hair relaxers? 🤔 Here’s what you need to know first! 

I totally get the appeal of hair relaxing treatments - they save time, are convenient, and help you look polished and put-together, especially for those who have their plates full. While I’m all for ✨embracing natural hair✨, I respect anyone’s choice to do things differently. 

But here’s why I’m not a fan :
👉🏽 Creates a barrier to hair color
👉🏽 Causes hair fall
👉🏽 It’s a trap as it only provides temporary relief 
👉🏽 Make hair look limp and lifeless

So, if you or your friends are considering these treatments, I’d suggest thinking it through carefully before committing, and making an informed choice rather than rushing into it. 🤓🙌🏽

Fire & Ice 🔥❄️
Warm and cool, two ends of the spectrum, both equally bold.
These beautiful ladies slayed these insane colours.
Right from the cut to the colour, everything was done keeping their personalities in mind.
Nothing fuels me like colour and cuts done with purpose, and these four gave me the kind of creative joy that keeps me obsessed.

Shubhika @shubhikasharma 
🎨 Haircolor: Frosted Ash
This was a bold, high contrast ash money piece.
The color was placed deliberately and confidently in the front, not subtle, not soft, but sharp and statement making.
💥 Bleach was used.
✂️ Haircut: The Butterfly Shag

Shraddha
🎨 Haircolor: Toasted Cinnamon
This no bleach dimensional beauty was warm and completely complimented her skin tone, making her appear brighter and fresher.
✨ No bleach was used.
✂️ Haircut: The Bixie (when a bob marries a pixie)

Shipra @shipra30 
🎨 Haircolor: Copper Cocoa
A striking, super dimensional balayage with a bold money piece.
Her brief was clear, copper and brown, and this blend brought the best of both together in one cohesive swirl.
💥 Bleach was used.
✂️ Haircut: Butterfly but make it Hot Hair Balloon 😏

Zeenia
🎨 Haircolor: Expensive Brunette
She was done with ash and wanted to return to something richer.
We gave her a cold brew chocolate base with soft dimension in burnt sugar, bringing in all the expensive brunette energy.
✨ No bleach was used.
✂️ Haircut: Face frame with inverted layers

Which one’s your vibe - warm or cool? Let me know your pick in the comments. 👇

Looks like a cinnamon roll, is a cinnamon roll 🥮🤎

Unpopular opinion, but ash tones don’t always lift up fairer skin tones.❌

For Anvita, we chose a vibrant, warm colour which brought out her natural glow - making her look radiant, fresh, and youthful. Brunettes and warm tones elevate ✅ fairer skin tones better than ash, which can make skin look dull, washed out and pale.

Finding the perfect color for your skin tone can make a world of difference. 🙌🏽

Swooing 🤤 over this toasty, cinnamon spice colour and cut for my boo Anvita!

It’s a beautiful SUNDAY 💞
Finally, she agreed!

I’ve always felt that girls have their whole life to grow their hair long.
Short hair is easier to manage, quicker for morning hairstyles, and honestly they just look their age (and so, so cute) 

But of course, I could never force her into something she didn’t want.
So we looked at old pictures, had lots of little chats, and I’m so happppy she arrived at this decision on her own.

Also… her cheeks deserve their moment while they last.
